'''以戰止戰'''（英語：'''{{lang|en|The war to end war}}'''）出自中國兵書《[[司馬法|司馬法]]·仁本》，「以戰去戰，雖戰可也。」，也是[[第一次世界大戰|第一次世界大戰]]衍生的一個詞彙，由英國作家及社會評論家[[赫伯特·乔治·威尔斯|赫伯特·乔治·威尔斯]]（{{lang|en|H. G. Wells}}）在報章出版的一系列文章而成，隨後更輯成《以戰止戰》(''{{lang|en|The War That Will End War}}'')一書，<ref>{{cite book |title=H.G. Wells: Traversing Time |last=Wagar |first=W. Warren |year=2004 |publisher=Wesleyan University Press |location= |isbn=978-0-8195-6725-3 |page=147 |url=http://books.google.ie/books?id=HExGaHDhVbUC&pg=PA148&dq |accessdate=2010-08-24 |archive-date=2013-12-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131217092248/http://books.google.ie/books?id=HExGaHDhVbUC&pg=PA148&dq |dead-url=no }}</ref>鼓吹只有通過戰爭結束[[德意志帝國|德國]]軍國主義造成的[[第一次世界大戰|第一次世界大戰]]戰爭。<ref name="Russell">{{cite book |title=The Collected Papers of Bertrand Russell |editor-last=Rempel |editor-first=Richard A. |year=2003 |publisher=Routledge |location= |isbn=978-0-415-10463-0 |page=10 |url=http://books.google.ie/books?id=h9vF8W1dW48C&pg=PA10 |accessdate=2010-08-24 |archive-date=2013-12-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131217092244/http://books.google.ie/books?id=h9vF8W1dW48C&pg=PA10 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

一戰期間，以戰止戰理論曾遭受懷疑，領導英國的戰時內閣首相[[大衛·勞合·喬治|大衛·勞合·喬治]]諷刺地說：「這一戰，就像下一場，是以戰止戰」（{{lang|en|This war, like the next war, is a war to end war.}}），批評戰爭無助阻止大戰，反而釀成下一次戰爭。<ref>{{cite book |title=A Book about American Politics |last=Stimpson |first=George William |year=1952 |publisher=Harper |location= |isbn= |page=365 |url=http://books.google.ie/books?id=5eQ5AAAAMAAJ&q=%22like+the+next%22+%22war+to+end+war%22+lloyd+george&dq=%22like+the+next%22+%22war+to+end+war%22+lloyd+george&hl=en&ei=s6tzTK2JOsWjOJf3zc0I&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=5&ved=0CEMQ6AEwBA |accessdate=2010-08-24 |archive-date=2012-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121026045113/http://books.google.ie/books?id=5eQ5AAAAMAAJ&q=%22like+the+next%22+%22war+to+end+war%22+lloyd+george&dq=%22like+the+next%22+%22war+to+end+war%22+lloyd+george&hl=en&ei=s6tzTK2JOsWjOJf3zc0I&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=5&ved=0CEMQ6AEwBA |dead-url=no }}</ref> 

英軍將領[[阿奇博尔德·韦维尔，第一代韦维尔伯爵|阿奇博爾德·珀西瓦爾·韋維爾]]更沮喪地批評[[巴黎和会_(1919年)|巴黎和會]]：「經過以戰止戰，他們（三巨頭）卻以和平結束和平（{{lang|en|After the 'war to end war', they seem to have been in Paris at making the 'Peace to end Peace'}}）。<ref>{{cite book |title=Worlds at War: The 2,500-year Struggle between East and West |last=Pagden |first=Anthony |year=2008 |publisher=Oxford University Press US |location= |isbn=978-0-19-923743-2 |page=407 |url=http://books.google.ie/books?id=m80kwkt8YW4C&pg=PA407&d |accessdate=2010-08-24 |archive-date=2013-12-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131217092238/http://books.google.ie/books?id=m80kwkt8YW4C&pg=PA407&d |dead-url=no }}</ref>  

美國作家[[沃尔特·李普曼|沃尔特·李普曼]]在1967年的[[新聞週刊|新聞週刊]]指，以戰止戰是一種妄想（{{lang|en|the delusion is that whatever war we are fighting is the war to end war}}）。<ref name="Safire">{{cite book |title=Safire's Political Dictionary |last=Safire |first=William |year=2008 |publisher=Oxford University Press US |isbn=978-0-19-534334-2 |pages=792–3 |url=http://books.google.ie/books?id=jK-0NPoMiYoC&pg=PA792&dq |accessdate=2010-08-24 |archive-date=2013-12-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131217084856/http://books.google.ie/books?id=jK-0NPoMiYoC&pg=PA792&dq |dead-url=no }}</ref>


